title: Area sports menu for Saturday, Oct. 24 - Fri, 23 Oct 2015 PST
text:

High school: Nonleague: Sandpoint at Grangeville, 6 p.m. Golf 
College men: Idaho at Price’s Give Em Five Intercollegiate at El Paso, Texas (second day). Hockey

College men: NWC: Whitworth at Pacific Lutheran, 2:30 p.m. NWAC: CC Spokane at Treasure Valley, 1:15 p.m.; North Idaho at Walla Walla, 2:15. College women: NWC: Linfield at Whitworth, noon. NWAC: CC Spokane at Treasure Valley, 11 a.m.; North Idaho at Walla Walla, noon.

High school girls: GNL: Pullman vs. Cheney at Cheney, noon; East Valley at Clarkston, 4 p.m. Tennis

College: WCC: Portland at Gonzaga, noon. Big Sky: Eastern Washington at Weber State, Idaho at Idaho State, both 6. SWAC: North Idaho at Eastern Utah, 1 p.m. 
High school: 5A state play-in game: Lake City vs. Rocky Mountain at Grangeville, 5 p.m. 4A state play-in game: Sandpoint vs. Middleton at Grangeville, 3 p.m. 3A state play-in game: Bonners Ferry vs. Emmett at Grangeville, 5 p.m. NE2B: Kettle Falls vs. Lind-Ritzville/Sprague at Ritzville, 12:30 p.m. Reardan at Davenport, Liberty at Colfax, Tekoa-Rosalia vs. Wilbur-Creston at Wilbur, all 2. NE1B North: Republic at Cusick, Curlew at Selkirk, Inchelium at Cusick, all noon. Republic at Selkirk, 4 p.m. NE1B South: Columbia vs. Odessa-Harrington at Harrrington, Almira/Coulee-Hartline at Wellpinit, both noon. 1A Division II at Lake City: Mullan vs. Kootenai, 9 a.m.; Lakeside (ID) vs. Clark Fork, 10:30. Off-track betting 
Coeur d’Alene Casino: Open 24 hours. Greyhound Park & Event Center: Dog racing: 9:15 a.m.; horse racing: 9:55. Northern Quest Resort and Casino: Horse racing: 9:55 a.m.
